sql:
SELECT sequence_type, sequence_length
FROM sequences
WHERE sequence_id = 0;

external_knowledge:
- A sequence is considered as frequently accessed if it has the highest number of accesses in the last 30 days; 
- If multiple sequences have the same highest number of accesses, the one with the highest number of successful accesses is ranked higher; 
- A successful access is defined as an access with the 'is_successful' flag set to 1.

- The 'Mouse Genome Project' is a large-scale project focused on sequencing the mouse genome; 
- The sequences mentioned in the query refer to genetic sequences from the project; 
- Sequence details include base, position, base position, value, log2, file format, sequence type, sequence length, quality score, and whether the sequence is paired-end; 
- Access information includes the type of access (view or download), result size, and success rate; 
- The report aims to provide insights into user access patterns and sequence utilization within the project.
